docs.lead_paragraph: Some months ago, we duly chronicled how one Mr. GARDEN, a Tipperary Justice of the Peace, with some (pounds)2,000 per annum of landed property, had attempted the abduction of Miss ARBURTHNOT, (a fair "Saxon,") with the aid of a band of raftians, firearms, a coach and-four, and sundry bottles of chloroform;
